main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects reported in Seattle, Washington during July 1955.
interesting points: Witnesses saw three white objects for about 30 minutes, which appeared to be the size of a star., The objects moved up and down and side to side., The objects may have been a balloon cluster reflecting city lights., The observer had four confirmed witnesses to validate the sighting., A second sighting on July 21 involved a round black object that appeared to go straight up.
sighted object: three white objects; one round black object
witness description: Civilian observer with additional witnesses present
